I"û<p>One problem that can leave your system unstable is dependencies or orphaned packages leaving after you uninstall a package.</p>

<p>This problem  can be solved by installing a tool called <strong>debfoster</strong>. It tracks what you have installed and ask you to uninstall dependencies files when you uninstalled a program.</p>

<p>{% highlight bash%}
//install
sudo apt-get install debfoster</p>

<p>//help
sudo debfoster â€“help</p>

<p>//create initial keeper
sudo debfoster -q</p>

<p>//system to conform to keeper
sudo debfoster -f</p>

<p>//check orphaned/dependencies files
sudo debfoster</p>

<p>{% endhighlight %}</p>

<p>More information: <a href="http://ubuntuforums.org/showthread.php?t=24403" target="_blank">using debfoster in practice</a></p>
